snippet.title: Jawbreaker II for the Apple II
snippet.description:
Came also out for:

Atari 8-bit
Commodore VIC-20
(Well, actually there is "Jawbreaker" for the Atari 2600 which is like that)


Game description:

In Jawbreaker II you, as a pair of teeth, have to collect dots, items and avoid Jawbreakers (which are the faces here) 

However, you can get power-ups which allow you to destroy the Jawbreakers, but the power-ups last only for a certain amount of time, so use them wisely!

Designed by Chuckles without ever seeing the original Atari 2600 version!

What I think:

Hum, it plays like Jawbreaker on the Atari 2600, but I liked Jawbreaker more.

Still, a nice game to play...
